00:00:52,520 --> 00:00:55,121
      narrator: to contain      
     the sounds of traffic,     

4
00:00:55,256 --> 00:00:58,591
      it's often necessary      
  to put up a wall of silence.  

5
00:00:58,726 --> 00:01:01,994
       noise-barrier walls      
    both absorb traffic noise   

6
00:01:01,996 --> 00:01:04,530
    and shield neighborhoods    
            from it.            

7
00:01:04,532 --> 00:01:07,733
    with stone or brick-like    
     textures on both sides,    

8
00:01:07,802 --> 00:01:10,403
       they even look good      
         on the street.         

9
00:01:14,208 --> 00:01:16,075
          in the 1970s,         

10
00:01:16,210 --> 00:01:19,678
       noise-barrier walls      
   were mainly drab concrete.   

11
00:01:19,714 --> 00:01:21,414
     fast forward to today,     

12
00:01:21,549 --> 00:01:24,483
  and the walls come in a range 
     of textures and designs    

13
00:01:24,619 --> 00:01:26,619
        for curb appeal.        

14
00:01:26,754 --> 00:01:29,221
       but of course, it's      
 their noise-absorbing qualities

15
00:01:29,290 --> 00:01:32,291
       that really improve      
        the neighborhood.       

16
00:01:32,360 --> 00:01:33,692
they're made from a wood shaving

17
00:01:33,728 --> 00:01:36,028
       and cement material      
       that's very porous,      

18
00:01:36,097 --> 00:01:39,698
     which allows the walls     
 to absorb sound and entrap it. 

19
00:01:39,734 --> 00:01:42,435
        production starts       
     with the raw shavings.     

20
00:01:42,437 --> 00:01:46,439
    a conveyor delivers them    
        to a hammer mill.       

21
00:01:46,441 --> 00:01:49,508
    inside, rotating hammers    
     force the wood shavings    

22
00:01:49,577 --> 00:01:51,777
    through a cutting screen.   

23
00:01:57,251 --> 00:01:59,452
        this carves them        
     into smaller particles     

24
00:01:59,587 --> 00:02:02,321
        of various sizes.       

25
00:02:02,323 --> 00:02:03,922
 it's this combination of sizes 

26
00:02:04,024 --> 00:02:06,658
        that will create        
    the noise-absorbing pores   

27
00:02:06,694 --> 00:02:08,427
     in the completed wall.     

28
00:02:11,399 --> 00:02:14,066
            they test           
a proprietary chemical solution,

29
00:02:14,068 --> 00:02:16,335
        that will be used       
  to treat the wood particles,  

30
00:02:16,404 --> 00:02:19,872
           and confirm          
  it's the right concentration. 

31
00:02:20,007 --> 00:02:22,941
     an auger then mixes it     
     into the wood particles    

32
00:02:22,977 --> 00:02:25,811
       until they're damp       
     and thoroughly coated.     

33
00:02:25,880 --> 00:02:27,212
     without this treatment,    

34
00:02:27,248 --> 00:02:30,483
       the wood particles       
   wouldn't bind with cement.   

35
00:02:30,518 --> 00:02:33,419
  it will also protect the wood 
           from decay.          

36
00:02:35,490 --> 00:02:38,824
in another mixer, they add water
 and a second chemical solution 

37
00:02:38,860 --> 00:02:42,328
       to further enhance       
      the binding process.      

38
00:02:47,501 --> 00:02:50,702
   the wood particles are now   
  primed and ready to be mixed  

39
00:02:50,738 --> 00:02:56,308
with a powdered mix of limestone
  clay called portland cement.  

40
00:02:56,444 --> 00:02:58,044
           the machine          
      works the ingredients     

41
00:02:58,179 --> 00:03:00,379
         until they form        
       a cohesive material      

42
00:03:00,448 --> 00:03:02,114
       that can be shaped.      

43
00:03:08,723 --> 00:03:10,722
         the next worker        
     sprays a release agent     

44
00:03:10,758 --> 00:03:12,892
  onto the stone-pattern liner. 

45
00:03:15,396 --> 00:03:19,398
       each mold will form      
    one noise barrier panel.    

46
00:03:19,533 --> 00:03:22,000
       the team transfers       
    the wood-and-cement blend   

47
00:03:22,070 --> 00:03:23,602
         into the mold.         

48
00:03:23,671 --> 00:03:25,070
   they work at a steady pace   

49
00:03:25,139 --> 00:03:28,207
  to fill it before the mixture 
         begins to dry.         

50
00:03:33,281 --> 00:03:35,080
 once they've filled it partway,

51
00:03:35,083 --> 00:03:37,450
           they level           
   the wood-cement material...  

52
00:03:39,554 --> 00:03:42,054
       ...then compact it       
      with a tamping tool.      

53
00:03:43,858 --> 00:03:46,425
  next, they add a steel mesh.  

54
00:03:46,494 --> 00:03:48,560
      this mesh will serve      
         as a skeleton,         

55
00:03:48,629 --> 00:03:51,897
        allowing the wall       
        to stand strong.        

56
00:03:51,966 --> 00:03:55,434
they pour freshly mixed concrete
      onto the steel mesh.      

57
00:03:55,569 --> 00:03:57,035
    it flows through the mesh   

58
00:03:57,071 --> 00:03:59,772
  and onto the sound-absorbing  
         mixture below,         

59
00:03:59,841 --> 00:04:02,441
binding the two layers together.

60
00:04:02,510 --> 00:04:05,678
 the worker spreads the concrete
      throughout the mold.      

61
00:04:07,315 --> 00:04:10,849
     he pierces the surface     
     with a vibrating tool.     

62
00:04:10,952 --> 00:04:13,452
         the vibrations         
    consolidate the concrete    

63
00:04:13,587 --> 00:04:15,721
   and eliminate air pockets.   

64
00:04:17,458 --> 00:04:19,057
   the two-person team levels   

65
00:04:19,093 --> 00:04:22,161
       the concrete layer       
      using a wood screed.      

66
00:04:30,671 --> 00:04:35,140
    they apply a second layer   
 of the noise-absorbing material

67
00:04:35,209 --> 00:04:37,076
          and level it.         

68
00:04:46,354 --> 00:04:48,621
           they lower           
  the stone-pattern press lid,  

69
00:04:48,623 --> 00:04:51,957
   which will mold the pattern  
 onto the top side of the panel.

70
00:04:54,562 --> 00:04:57,429
they set a 10-ton concrete block
          on the mold,          

71
00:04:57,498 --> 00:04:59,365
       and pressure forces      
        the mold patterns       

72
00:04:59,500 --> 00:05:01,634
 onto both sides of the casting.

73
00:05:05,173 --> 00:05:06,772
      after a few minutes,      

74
00:05:06,774 --> 00:05:11,409
      they remove the lid,      
  and the imprint is revealed.  

75
00:05:11,445 --> 00:05:14,579
  they quickly cover the panel  
  surface with a plastic sheet  

76
00:05:14,615 --> 00:05:16,982
   to prevent any evaporation   
           of moisture          

77
00:05:17,051 --> 00:05:19,184
     as the cure continues.     

78
00:05:19,253 --> 00:05:21,120
 if the blend cures too quickly,

79
00:05:21,255 --> 00:05:23,455
         it could crack.        

80
00:05:23,457 --> 00:05:25,791
       after another day,       
      they remove the tarp      

81
00:05:25,926 --> 00:05:28,961
  and they're ready to extract  
    the panel from the mold.    

82
00:05:30,531 --> 00:05:32,131
     a crane lifts the panel    

83
00:05:32,133 --> 00:05:35,134
        and sets it aside       
   to cure for about a month.   

84
00:05:39,540 --> 00:05:41,139
      built panel by panel,     

85
00:05:41,175 --> 00:05:45,010
  these noise-barrier walls can 
 become a substantial fortress, 

86
00:05:45,145 --> 00:05:48,714
    providing a solid defense   
    against noise pollution.    

