00:06:05,833 --> 00:06:07,099
            narrator:           
 front-loading washing machines 

88
00:06:07,168 --> 00:06:09,968
       use far less water       
     than standard washers.     

89
00:06:10,004 --> 00:06:12,838
   they're gentler on clothes   
   because there's no agitator  

90
00:06:12,840 --> 00:06:15,040
   in the middle of the drum.   

91
00:06:15,076 --> 00:06:16,575
    the spin speed is usually   

92
00:06:16,577 --> 00:06:19,979
  about 20 percent faster than  
 the standard top-load machine, 

93
00:06:20,114 --> 00:06:22,882
         so the clothes         
   come out of the wash drier.  

94
00:06:26,454 --> 00:06:30,055
   with gravity helping tumble  
the laundry, a front-load washer

95
00:06:30,124 --> 00:06:34,059
    is gentler on the clothes   
     while using less water.    

96
00:06:34,061 --> 00:06:37,730
 its design can also accommodate
     a larger-capacity drum,    

97
00:06:37,865 --> 00:06:39,999
   so you can do bigger loads.  

98
00:06:40,134 --> 00:06:42,601
      the washer's cabinet      
        is made of steel.       

99
00:06:42,603 --> 00:06:45,938
 a washing machine is routinely 
      exposed to moisture,      

100
00:06:46,007 --> 00:06:50,276
  so they use galvanized steel, 
       which doesn't rust.      

101
00:06:50,411 --> 00:06:53,479
  the cabinet base is comprised 
         of four pieces,        

102
00:06:53,614 --> 00:06:56,281
        which, together,        
provide more structural strength

103
00:06:56,317 --> 00:06:57,882
   than a single piece would.   

104
00:06:57,952 --> 00:07:01,553
 at the corners, workers install
    four screw-in rubber feet   

105
00:07:01,656 --> 00:07:03,221
  which are height-adjustable.  

106
00:07:03,257 --> 00:07:06,625
     this allows the washer     
  to level on an uneven floor.  

107
00:07:06,727 --> 00:07:08,894
  next are the two side panels. 

108
00:07:08,896 --> 00:07:12,031
    they are already stamped    
to the required shape in a press

109
00:07:12,166 --> 00:07:14,332
 and coated with baked-on paint.

110
00:07:14,368 --> 00:07:17,836
 this automated machine installs
   brackets on the inner side   

111
00:07:17,905 --> 00:07:18,837
     for mounting components    

112
00:07:18,973 --> 00:07:20,372
            later on.           

113
00:07:20,374 --> 00:07:23,108
   the next automated machine   
    attaches the side panels    

114
00:07:23,144 --> 00:07:24,777
         to the cabinet.        

115
00:07:24,779 --> 00:07:26,445
 rather than welding the edges, 

116
00:07:26,580 --> 00:07:28,314
        which would ruin        
        the paint finish,       

117
00:07:28,449 --> 00:07:29,648
    the machine's punch tools   

118
00:07:29,783 --> 00:07:32,584
          mechanically          
     lock them to the base.     

119
00:07:32,620 --> 00:07:37,056
   a robot then transfers the   
  cabinet to the assembly line. 

120
00:07:38,225 --> 00:07:40,191
          here, workers         
     connect the side panels    

121
00:07:40,227 --> 00:07:43,028
    with a structural support   
     bracket and power cord,    

122
00:07:43,064 --> 00:07:44,930
    already installed on it.    

123
00:07:44,932 --> 00:07:46,531
workers prepare the rear portion

124
00:07:46,600 --> 00:07:49,201
        of the machine's        
     two-piece plastic tub.     

125
00:07:49,203 --> 00:07:53,138
      first, a robot mounts     
   a steel bearing on a press.  

126
00:07:53,174 --> 00:07:54,806
         the press then         
       forces the bearing       

127
00:07:54,875 --> 00:07:58,410
    into a hole at the bottom   
    of the inside of the tub.   

128
00:07:58,412 --> 00:08:02,547
  then the process is repeated  
 but on the outside of the tub. 

129
00:08:02,616 --> 00:08:05,683
      this pair of bearings     
seals the hole to prevent leaks,

130
00:08:05,720 --> 00:08:09,388
 and enables the stainless-steel
       wash drum to spin.       

131
00:08:11,425 --> 00:08:13,625
        to counterbalance       
       the spinning load,       

132
00:08:13,694 --> 00:08:16,494
      they weight the front     
of the drum with a plastic ring,

133
00:08:16,530 --> 00:08:20,799
  containing heavy steel balls  
       suspended in fluid.      

134
00:08:20,901 --> 00:08:23,302
   then, they insert the shaft  
     at the base of the drum    

135
00:08:23,437 --> 00:08:25,037
     into the tub's bearings    

136
00:08:25,172 --> 00:08:27,572
  and cover the top of the drum 
     with the front section     

137
00:08:27,608 --> 00:08:28,840
           of the tub.          

138
00:08:28,909 --> 00:08:31,643
     it has a rubber gasket     
        called a bellow.        

139
00:08:31,712 --> 00:08:35,847
  the bellow forms a leak-proof 
      seal around the drum.     

140
00:08:35,883 --> 00:08:38,183
 after welding the tub sections 
            together,           

141
00:08:38,252 --> 00:08:40,919
  they mount the washer's motor 
          to the rear.          

142
00:08:41,055 --> 00:08:44,589
   in this stator-rotor motor,  
  the electric current travels  

143
00:08:44,658 --> 00:08:47,526
 through the coiled copper wires
     of the motor's stator,     

144
00:08:47,595 --> 00:08:50,662
        generating pulses       
         of electricity.        

145
00:08:50,698 --> 00:08:54,199
  those pulses push on magnets  
    lining the motor's rotor,   

146
00:08:54,201 --> 00:08:56,268
       positioned on top.       

147
00:08:56,403 --> 00:08:58,337
  the magnets repel the pulses, 

148
00:08:58,339 --> 00:09:00,072
        and this repeated       
         pulse repelling        

149
00:09:00,141 --> 00:09:04,543
drives the drum in the direction
       and speed required.      

150
00:09:04,678 --> 00:09:08,814
 next, they install a drain hose
     on the side of the tub     

151
00:09:08,916 --> 00:09:11,250
          and attach it         
      with a retainer clip.     

152
00:09:13,353 --> 00:09:16,755
they bolt a piece of concrete to
 either side of the drum opening

153
00:09:16,824 --> 00:09:20,225
  to counterbalance the weight  
    of the motor on the back.   

154
00:09:20,227 --> 00:09:23,695
then, they turn the now-complete
      wash unit on its side     

155
00:09:23,764 --> 00:09:25,964
 and install it in the cabinet. 

156
00:09:29,236 --> 00:09:32,838
 next, they mount the drain pump
       in the cabinet base      

157
00:09:32,973 --> 00:09:34,773
     and connect its wiring.    

158
00:09:34,842 --> 00:09:39,111
   the pump's job is to remove  
    dirty water from the tub.   

159
00:09:40,981 --> 00:09:42,981
      four shock absorbers      
          are installed         

160
00:09:43,117 --> 00:09:46,785
       between the bottom       
 of the wash unit and the base. 

161
00:09:46,854 --> 00:09:49,655
   these large pistons dampen   
      much of the vibration     

162
00:09:49,790 --> 00:09:52,191
during the wash and spin cycles.

163
00:09:53,594 --> 00:09:55,193
     next, the front panel.     

164
00:09:55,262 --> 00:09:57,729
         like the sides,        
  it's made of a stamped sheet  

165
00:09:57,731 --> 00:10:01,066
       of galvanized steel      
  with a baked-on paint finish. 

166
00:10:02,636 --> 00:10:04,469
    they install and connect    
          the console,          

167
00:10:04,505 --> 00:10:07,506
   which houses the machine's   
     central control module.    

168
00:10:10,477 --> 00:10:13,678
they pull the bellow on the drum
  all around the front opening  

169
00:10:13,714 --> 00:10:15,547
     to seal the perimeter.     

170
00:10:19,553 --> 00:10:23,388
     they secure it in place    
   with a wire retainer clip.   

171
00:10:28,362 --> 00:10:31,630
       the hinged door has      
  a see-through plastic window. 

172
00:10:31,632 --> 00:10:33,966
          like the rest         
  of the machine's metal parts, 

173
00:10:34,101 --> 00:10:36,702
         the door panel         
    and hardware attaching it   

174
00:10:36,704 --> 00:10:40,371
          are also made         
      of galvanized steel.      

175
00:10:40,407 --> 00:10:42,841
         the back panel         
       is left unpainted.       

176
00:10:42,843 --> 00:10:45,310
  after feeding the power cord  
        through its hole,       

177
00:10:45,445 --> 00:10:49,314
     workers screw the panel    
   to the rest of the cabinet.  

178
00:10:49,449 --> 00:10:52,116
 then, they complete the cabinet
       with the top panel,      

179
00:10:52,153 --> 00:10:54,620
  which has the baked-on paint  
             finish.            

180
00:10:56,423 --> 00:10:57,856
 the front-load washing machine 

181
00:10:57,991 --> 00:11:02,060
         is now all set         
  and ready for its first load. 

